snippet.textDisplay: Kinda like shining a turd but you did an awesome job! Sadly I sent my Trail blazer to the scrap with a perfect interior.  I learned detailing by the owner / director of our local funeral home. My first real job was washing funeral home cars.  The owner showed me the way to detail a vehicle. The cars he had were White. I have since always cleaned and detailed  vehicles like he showed me. I do carpets like I was taught while being a custodian.I use a pump sprayer for the cleaner and use only water in the extractor for rinsing. This removes the cleaner so no soap residue can remain in the carpet to attract dirt later when humidity causes the soap residue to attract dirt faster. learned that doing carpet runners. By using a clear water extract,  it eliminated the salt trail that built up faster due to soap still in the runner.
